<br>
If your guild/raid party doesn't have a person on allied Chardok faction, then you getting allied faction in Chardok will help with royal raids a ton! You will be very helpful with CR, scouting, and you can hail pull the queen single.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, is your guild going to let you loot that queen blade if you don't actually participate in meleeing her to death? Figure that one out first. Once you do Chardok faction, you really don't want to kill there anymore. I double boxed my way to ally faction, my warrior was at bottomed out and it took 2000 faction hits to get to threatening! It took almost that many (1800-2000) to go from threatening to ally. That's going to be a lot of wasted effort if you trash your Chardok faction on a royals raid... if you're going to ruin it, don't bother wasting your time trying to get Chardok faction now. <p><p><map name="FPMap0">
